- Partial rollout is effectively bypassed for `isFileWatcherEnabled` and `isLocalRerankerEnabled` when rollout is 1-99, despite comments saying rollout is honored. They call `isFeatureEnabled(...)` without identity ([search-flags.ts:197](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts:197), [search-flags.ts:207](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts:207)); `isFeatureEnabled` returns `true` when identity is missing ([rollout-policy.ts:45](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:45)). Comment claims at [search-flags.ts:193](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts:193), [search-flags.ts:203](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts:203).
- `getRolloutPercent` uses `parseInt`, so malformed numeric strings are silently accepted/truncated (e.g. `50abc` -> 50, `1e2` -> 1) before clamp ([rollout-policy.ts:13](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:13), [rollout-policy.ts:18](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:18)).

**Minor**
- Empty string or non-`false`/`0` textual values (e.g. `""`, `off`, `no`) are treated as enabled by design; operationally easy to misconfigure ([rollout-policy.ts:37](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:37), [rollout-policy.ts:39](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:39)).
- Identity is only trimmed for emptiness check, not normalized before hashing; whitespace-variant identities can bucket differently ([rollout-policy.ts:45](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:45), [rollout-policy.ts:49](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:49), [rollout-policy.ts:23](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cache/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts:23)).

